<subSubSection id="6EDC654FFE44FF8FFF0AFE9E5F13FDBD" pageId="4" pageNumber="25" type="description">
<paragraph id="267936C4FE44FF8FFF0AFE9E5D15FE3D" blockId="4.[166,1225,335,522]" pageId="4" pageNumber="25">
D i s t r i b u t i o n. Most of Eurasia. 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE44FF8FFDBBFE9E5ED9FEDD" box="[618,671,336,362]" name="Iran" pageId="4" pageNumber="25">Iran</collectingCountry>
: Yano (1987); 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE44FF8FFC9FFE815D09FE3D" author="Seddighi Sadr, F. &amp; Mohammadzade Namin, S." pageId="4" pageNumber="25" pagination="43 - 45" refId="ref6894" refString="Seddighi Sadr, F., Mohammadzade Namin, S. 2016. The snail killing flies (Diptera, Sciomyzidae) in Gilan Province, with a new record for Iranian fauna. Ukrainska Entomofaunistyka, 7 (1), 43 - 45." type="journal article" year="2016">Seddighi Sadr, Mohammadzade Namin (2016)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="267936C4FE44FF8FFF0AFE415F13FDBD" blockId="4.[166,1225,335,522]" pageId="4" pageNumber="25">
Biology. 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE44FF8FFE8BFE5E5E1DFE1D" author="Knutson, L. V. &amp; Rozkosny, R. &amp; Berg, C. O." box="[346,603,399,426]" pageId="4" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 38" refId="ref6499" refString="Knutson, L. V., Rozkosny, R., Berg, C. O. 1975. Biology and immature stages of Pherbina and Psacadina (Diptera: Sciomyzidae). Acta Scientiarum Naturlium Academiae Scientiarm Bohemicae Brno, 9 (1), 1 - 38." type="journal article" year="1975">Knutson et al. (1975)</bibRefCitation>
studied the larval development of this species, and described all immature stages. The larvae are predators of various freshwater and terrestrial gastropods, also hygrophilous Succinids (
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE44FF8FFD47FE015FC8FE5D" author="Knutson, L. V. &amp; Rozkosny, R. &amp; Berg, C. O." box="[662,910,463,490]" pageId="4" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 38" refId="ref6499" refString="Knutson, L. V., Rozkosny, R., Berg, C. O. 1975. Biology and immature stages of Pherbina and Psacadina (Diptera: Sciomyzidae). Acta Scientiarum Naturlium Academiae Scientiarm Bohemicae Brno, 9 (1), 1 - 38." type="journal article" year="1975">Knutson et al., 1975</bibRefCitation>
). The species is univoltine and overwintering as a third-instar larva (
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE44FF8FFD5EFE215F0CFDBD" author="Gaponov, S. P." box="[655,842,495,522]" pageId="4" pageNumber="25" pagination="54 - 63" refId="ref6197" refString="Gaponov, S. P. 2016. Fauna and bioecology of snail-killing flies (Diptera: Sciomyzidae) in the central black soil region of Russia. Proceedings of Voronezh State University. Ser.: Chemistry. Biology. Pharmacy, 1, 54 - 63." type="journal article" year="2016">Gaponov, 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
